      "magicItemType": "magicMisc",
      "name": "Scroll of Detect Magic",
      "bonus": 0,
      "bonusNote": "",
      "attackNote": "",
      "features": "This scroll allows a character to cast the Detect Magic spell if that spell is on their spell list (even if they don't know that spell). Failing to cast the spell from the scroll does not impact the ability to cast known spells. After a casting attempt with a scroll, the scroll ceases to work. On a critical failure, casters with mishap tables must roll a mishap. ",
      "spellDesc": "DETECT MAGIC (Tier 1, Wizard), DC 10 to cast, Duration: Focus, Range: Near \n You can sense the presence of magic within near range for the spell's duration. If you focus for two rounds, you discern its general properties. Full barriers block this spell.",
